HEADWORD: Musculospiral
<hw>Mus`cu*lo*spi"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>musculus</ets> muscle + E. <ets>spiral</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the muscles, and taking a
spiral course; -- applied esp. to a large nerve of the arm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Musculous</ent>⟦br⟧
